info:
  contact: {email: frikky@shuffler.io, name: '@frikkylikeme', url: 'https://twitter.com/frikkylikeme'}
  description: Automated generation of Cisco Firepower Threat Defense
  title: Cisco Firepower Threat Defense

openapi: 3.0.2
paths:
  tmp0:
    post:
      description: Create a URL Object
      parameters:
      - description: A string represents the name of URL object.
        example: Google
        in: query
        name: Name
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: A string value containing the URL address.
        example: www.example.com
        in: query
        name: URL
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: An string containing the description information of URL object.
        example: This string describes the URL.
        in: query
        name: Description
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp0'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Cisco Firepower Threat Defense Create URL Object
  tmp1:
    post:
      description: Delete a URL Object
      parameters:
      - description: A unique string identifier assigned by the system when the object
          is created.
        example: 41f286f8-f04a-11e9-96f1-cd2f55287c3a
        in: query
        name: URL ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp1'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Cisco Firepower Threat Defense Delete URL Object
  tmp2:
    post:
      description: Audit Object by ID
      parameters:
      - description: A unique string identifier assigned by the system when the object
          is created.
        example: 41f286f8-f04a-11e9-96f1-cd2f55287c3a
        in: query
        name: Audit Event ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp2'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Cisco Firepower Threat Defense Get Audit Event By ID
  tmp3:
    post:
      description: Get All Audit Objects
      parameters:
      - description: Filter Out System Events
        example: 'True'
        in: query
        name: Filter Out System Events
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: A List of Filters, CSV
        example: type:auditentityupdateevent,timestamp:1571958762940
        in: query
        name: Filter
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Date
        example: 10/20/2019
        in: query
        name: Date
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Limit the number of returned entries, default value is 500.
        example: '200'
        in: query
        name: Limit
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp3'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Cisco Firepower Threat Defense Get All Audit Events
  tmp4:
    post:
      description: Get URL Object by ID
      parameters:
      - description: A unique string identifier assigned by the system when the object
          is created.
        example: 41f286f8-f04a-11e9-96f1-cd2f55287c3a
        in: query
        name: URL ID
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp4'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Cisco Firepower Threat Defense Get URL Object By ID
  tmp5:
    post:
      description: Get URL Objects
      parameters:
      - description: Limit the number of returned entries, default value is 500.
        example: '200'
        in: query
        name: Limit
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp5'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Cisco Firepower Threat Defense Get All URL Objects
  tmp6:
    post:
      description: Update URL Object by ID
      parameters:
      - description: A string represents the name of URL object.
        example: This is an example name
        in: query
        name: Name
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: A string value containing the URL address.
        example: www.google.com
        in: query
        name: URL
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: A unique string version assigned by the system when the object
          is created or modified.
        example: cn5hn247vklyl
        in: query
        name: Version
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: A unique string identifier assigned by the system when the object
          is created.
        example: 8f6d8034-f5b3-11e9-96f1-d1bce0a8cc88
        in: query
        name: URL ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: A string containing the description information of URL object.
        example: Basic Description of the URL Object
        in: query
        name: Description
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp6'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Cisco Firepower Threat Defense Update URL Object
tags:
